#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:81
msgid "Key rules:"
msgstr "关键规则："

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:82
msgid ""
"**Don't `use perry_runtime::*`**. perry-runtime's internals (NaN-box tags, "
"struct layouts) change between Perry releases. perry-ffi is the stable "
"contract."
msgstr ""
"**不要使用 `use perry_runtime::*`**。perry-runtime 的内部实现（NaN-box 标签、结构体布局）会在 "
"Perry 版本之间变化。perry-ffi 才是稳定的契约。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:85
msgid ""
"**Use `unsafe extern \"C\"` for any function that takes pointer args**. "
"`*const StringHeader` etc. require unsafe at the call site."
msgstr ""
"**对接受指针参数的任何函数使用 `unsafe extern \"C\"`**。`*const StringHeader` 等类型在调用点要求 "
"unsafe。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:87
msgid ""
"**Document `# Safety` for unsafe fns** — at minimum say \"the pointer must "
"be null or a Perry-runtime `<Header>`\"."
msgstr ""
"**为 unsafe 函数编写 `# Safety` 文档** —— 至少要写明“该指针必须为 null 或一个 Perry-runtime "
"`<Header>`”。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:89
msgid ""
"**Async returns `*mut Promise`**. Pattern: `JsPromise::new()` → "
"`spawn_blocking(move || { tokio::runtime::Handle::current().block_on(async "
"{...}); promise.resolve(...) })` → return `promise.as_raw()`."
msgstr ""
"**异步返回 `*mut Promise`**。模式：`JsPromise::new()` → `spawn_blocking(move || { "
"tokio::runtime::Handle::current().block_on(async {...}); "
"promise.resolve(...) })` → 返回 `promise.as_raw()`。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:93
msgid "`src/index.ts`"
msgstr "`src/index.ts`"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:95
msgid ""
"Declare the FFI symbol from your manifest, then export the TypeScript "
"surface user code imports. Perry's FFI dispatch keys on the call-site "
"identifier, so the wrapper body must explicitly call the `js_*` symbol "
"listed in `perry.nativeLibrary.functions[]`."
msgstr ""
"从你的 manifest 中声明 FFI 符号，然后导出用户代码所导入的 TypeScript 接口。Perry 的 FFI "
"派发以调用点标识符为键，因此 wrapper 函数体必须显式调用 `perry.nativeLibrary.functions[]` 中列出的 "
"`js_*` 符号。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:111 src/cli/perry-toml.md:557
#: src/cli/perry-toml.md:558
