#: src/container/containers.md:132
msgid ""
"**Note on the `logs` and `exec` return shape:** today the FFI returns a "
"registry-id handle into a `Vec<ContainerLogs>` rather than a JS object. "
"Treat the returned value as opaque — a future ergonomics task will expose "
"`.stdout` / `.stderr` directly on the JS side. The `ContainerLogs` shape "
"over the wire is `{ stdout: string, stderr: string }`."
msgstr ""
"**关于 `logs` 和 `exec` 返回值的说明：** 目前 FFI 返回的是指向 `Vec<ContainerLogs>` 中某一条目的注册表 "
"ID 句柄，而非 JS 对象。请将返回值视为不透明值——未来的易用性改进任务将在 JS 侧直接暴露 `.stdout` / "
"`.stderr`。`ContainerLogs` 在传输层的结构为 `{ stdout: string, stderr: string }`。"

#: src/container/containers.md:139
msgid "Image management"
msgstr "镜像管理"

#: src/container/containers.md:141
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { pullImage, listImages, removeImage } from \"perry/container\";\n"
"\n"
"async function manageImages(): Promise<void> {\n"
"    await pullImage(\"postgres:16-alpine\");\n"
"    const images = await listImages();\n"
"    console.log(`${images.length} images`);\n"
"    await removeImage(\"postgres:16-alpine\", false);\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/containers.md:154
msgid "`pullImage(reference)`"
msgstr "`pullImage(reference)`"

#: src/container/containers.md:154
msgid "`(reference: string) → Promise<void>`"
msgstr "`(reference: string) → Promise<void>`"

#: src/container/containers.md:155
msgid "`listImages()`"
msgstr "`listImages()`"

#: src/container/containers.md:155
msgid "`() → Promise<ImageInfo[]>`"
msgstr "`() → Promise<ImageInfo[]>`"

#: src/container/containers.md:156
msgid "`removeImage(reference, force?)`"
msgstr "`removeImage(reference, force?)`"

#: src/container/containers.md:156
