#: src/container/networking.md:3
msgid ""
"Compose stacks join one or more user-defined networks. Each container spec "
"lists the networks it joins; the engine creates the networks (if they don't "
"already exist) before starting any service. This page covers the day-to-day "
"networking patterns Perry users hit."
msgstr ""
"Compose 栈加入一个或多个用户自定义网络。每个容器规格列出其所加入的网络；引擎在启动任何服务之前会先创建这些网络（若不存在）。本页介绍 Perry"
" 用户常见的日常网络使用模式。"

#: src/container/networking.md:8
msgid "Defining networks"
msgstr "定义网络"

#: src/container/networking.md:10
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const stack = await up({\n"
"  version: \"3.8\",\n"
"  services: {\n"
"    api: { image: \"myapp/api\", networks: [\"app-net\"] },\n"
"    db:  { image: \"postgres:16-alpine\", networks: [\"app-net\"] },\n"
"  },\n"
"  networks: {\n"
"    \"app-net\": { driver: \"bridge\" },\n"
"  },\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/networking.md:23
msgid "Recognised `ComposeNetwork` fields:"
msgstr "已识别的 `ComposeNetwork` 字段："

#: src/container/networking.md:27 src/container/volumes.md:39
msgid "`driver`"
msgstr "`driver`"

#: src/container/networking.md:27
msgid "Network driver (`\"bridge\"` is the default; `\"overlay\"` for swarm)."
msgstr "网络驱动（默认为 `\"bridge\"`；集群模式使用 `\"overlay\"`）。"

#: src/container/networking.md:28 src/container/volumes.md:40
msgid "`external`"
msgstr "`external`"

#: src/container/networking.md:28
msgid "Don't create — assume the network already exists."
msgstr "不创建——假定网络已存在。"

#: src/container/networking.md:29
msgid "Override the network's runtime name."
msgstr "覆盖网络的运行时名称。"

#: src/container/networking.md:30
msgid "`internal`"
msgstr "`internal`"

#: src/container/networking.md:30
msgid ""
"**Internal-only**: containers attached have no external bridge or routing. "
"See below."
msgstr "**仅限内部**：连接的容器无外部网桥或路由。详见下文。"

#: src/container/networking.md:31
msgid "`driver_opts`"
msgstr "`driver_opts`"

#: src/container/networking.md:31
msgid "Driver-specific options."
msgstr "驱动专用选项。"

#: src/container/networking.md:32
msgid "Network labels."
msgstr "网络标签。"

#: src/container/networking.md:34
msgid "Internal-only networks (`internal: true`)"
msgstr "仅限内部网络（`internal: true`）"

#: src/container/networking.md:36
msgid ""
"A network with `internal: true` blocks egress to anything outside the "
"network. Containers on it can talk to each other, but **cannot reach the "
"host or the public internet**, and the host cannot reach them via published "
"ports. This is the canonical \"private database side-channel\" pattern:"
msgstr ""
"设置了 `internal: true` "
"的网络会阻止流量出口到网络外部。其上的容器可以相互通信，但**无法访问宿主机或公共互联网**，宿主机也无法通过已发布的端口访问它们。这是典型的“私有数据库侧信道”模式："

#: src/container/networking.md:42
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"networks: {\n"
"  \"app-db-net\":  { driver: \"bridge\", internal: true },  // db <-> api only\n"
"  \"app-web-net\": { driver: \"bridge\" },                  // api <-> host\n"
"},\n"
"services: {\n"
"  db: {\n"
"    image: \"postgres:16-alpine\",\n"
"    networks: [\"app-db-net\"],   // db is reachable ONLY from app-db-net\n"
"    // no `ports:` — postgres is unpublished\n"
"  },\n"
"  api: {\n"
"    image: \"myapp/api\",\n"
"    networks: [\"app-db-net\", \"app-web-net\"],\n"
"    ports: [\"8080:8080\"],       // api published on the host\n"
"  },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/networking.md:61
msgid ""
"The api container straddles both networks: it can reach `db` over `app-db-"
"net` and accept inbound HTTP from the host on `app-web-net`. postgres is "
"invisible to anything not on `app-db-net`."
msgstr ""
"api 容器同时跨越两个网络：它可以通过 `app-db-net` 访问 `db`，并可在 `app-web-net` 上接受来自宿主机的入站 HTTP"
" 请求。postgres 对不在 `app-db-net` 上的任何节点均不可见。"

#: src/container/networking.md:67
msgid ""
"Within a user-defined bridge network, docker's embedded DNS resolves "
"container names to IP addresses. So if a service's `container_name` is "
"`forgejo-db`, sibling containers on the same network can connect to it as "
"`forgejo-db:5432`."
msgstr ""
"在用户自定义的桥接网络中，Docker 内置 DNS 会将容器名称解析为 IP 地址。因此，若某服务的 `container_name` 为 "
"`forgejo-db`，同一网络上的兄弟容器可通过 `forgejo-db:5432` 连接到它。"

#: src/container/networking.md:72
msgid ""
"⚠️ **Important:** Perry's compose engine generates per-service container "
"names of the form `{md5(image)[0..8]}-{random_hex8}` by default. It does "
"**not** (yet) register the service KEY (`db`, `api`, …) as a network alias "
"the way `docker compose` does. So a config like:"
msgstr ""
"⚠️ **重要提示：** Perry 的 compose 引擎默认以 `{md5(image)[0..8]}-{random_hex8}` "
"的形式生成每个服务的容器名称。它（目前）**不会**像 `docker compose` 那样将服务键（`db`、`api` "
"等）注册为网络别名。因此以下配置："

#: src/container/networking.md:78
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"api: {\n"
"  image: \"myapp/api\",\n"
"  environment: {\n"
"    DATABASE_URL: \"postgres://user:pw@db:5432/app\",  // ❌ \"db\" doesn't resolve\n"
"  },\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/networking.md:87
msgid ""
"will fail at runtime with `dial tcp: lookup db on 127.0.0.11:53: no such "
"host`. **Until service-key network aliasing lands, set `container_name` "
"explicitly** and use those names in sibling URLs:"
msgstr ""
"将在运行时以 `dial tcp: lookup db on 127.0.0.11:53: no such host` "
"失败。**在服务键网络别名功能落地之前，请显式设置 `container_name`**，并在兄弟服务 URL 中使用这些名称："

#: src/container/networking.md:91
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// IMPORTANT: Perry's compose engine creates each container with a\n"
"// `{md5}-{random_hex}` derived name and DOES NOT (yet) register the\n"
"// service KEY (`db`, `api`, …) as a network alias. So\n"
"// `DATABASE_URL: 'postgres://user:pw@db:5432/app'` would fail name\n"
"// resolution at runtime. Two ways to make sibling-DNS work:\n"
"//\n"
"//   (a) Set `container_name` explicitly on each service so the\n"
"//       chosen name is what Docker's embedded DNS resolves. This is\n"
"//       the simplest pattern and is what the Forgejo example uses.\n"
"//\n"
"//   (b) Wait for service-key network-alias support (planned).\n"
"//\n"
"// Until (b) lands, prefer (a):\n"
"import { up as upDns } from \"perry/compose\";\n"
"\n"
"async function dnsAwareStack(): Promise<void> {\n"
"    await upDns({\n"
"        version: \"3.8\",\n"
"        services: {\n"
"            db: {\n"
"                image: \"postgres:16-alpine\",\n"
"                container_name: \"myapp-db\", // ← stable DNS target\n"
"                networks: [\"myapp-net\"],\n"
"                environment: { POSTGRES_PASSWORD: \"x\" },\n"
"            },\n"
"            api: {\n"
"                image: \"myapp/api\",\n"
"                container_name: \"myapp-api\",\n"
"                networks: [\"myapp-net\"],\n"
"                environment: {\n"
"                    // Use the container_name as the hostname:\n"
"                    DATABASE_URL: \"postgres://postgres:x@myapp-db:5432/postgres\",\n"
"                },\n"
"            },\n"
"        },\n"
"        networks: { \"myapp-net\": { driver: \"bridge\" } },\n"
"    });\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/networking.md:132
msgid ""
"The Forgejo example uses this pattern (`container_name: 'forgejo-db'` + "
"`FORGEJO__database__HOST: 'forgejo-db:5432'`). It's a documented workaround "
"that keeps user code idiomatic; replacing `container_name` with service-key "
"alias registration is a planned runtime change that will not require any "
"user-facing API change."
msgstr ""
"Forgejo 示例使用了此模式（`container_name: 'forgejo-db'` + `FORGEJO__database__HOST: "
"'forgejo-db:5432'`）。这是一个已记录的变通方案，使用户代码保持符合习惯；将 `container_name` "
"替换为服务键别名注册是计划中的 runtime 变更，届时不需要任何面向用户的 API 更改。"

#: src/container/networking.md:138
msgid "Port mapping"
msgstr "端口映射"

#: src/container/networking.md:140
msgid ""
"Inside a service spec, `ports: [\"host:container[:proto]\"]` publishes ports"
" to the host. Examples:"
msgstr "在服务规范内，`ports: [\"host:container[:proto]\"]` 将端口发布到主机。示例："

#: src/container/networking.md:143 src/container/networking.md:183
msgid "Spec"
msgstr "规范"

#: src/container/networking.md:145
msgid "`\"8080:80\"`"
msgstr "`\"8080:80\"`"

#: src/container/networking.md:145
msgid "Host port 8080 → container port 80 (TCP)."
msgstr "主机端口 8080 → 容器端口 80（TCP）。"

#: src/container/networking.md:146
msgid "`\"8080:80/udp\"`"
msgstr "`\"8080:80/udp\"`"

#: src/container/networking.md:146
msgid "Host port 8080 → container port 80 (UDP)."
msgstr "主机端口 8080 → 容器端口 80（UDP）。"

#: src/container/networking.md:147
msgid "`\"127.0.0.1:8080:80\"`"
msgstr "`\"127.0.0.1:8080:80\"`"

#: src/container/networking.md:147
msgid "Bind only to loopback on the host (don't expose to other LAN hosts)."
msgstr "仅绑定到主机的回环地址（不向其他 LAN 主机暴露）。"

#: src/container/networking.md:148
msgid "`\"3000-3010:3000-3010\"`"
msgstr "`\"3000-3010:3000-3010\"`"

#: src/container/networking.md:148
msgid "Range mapping (UDP/TCP, host:container both inclusive)."
msgstr "范围映射（UDP/TCP，主机与容器两端均包含）。"

#: src/container/networking.md:150
msgid ""
"For services that should never be host-published (private databases, "
"internal-only side-cars), simply **don't list any ports**. Combined with "
"`internal: true` on the network, those services are unreachable from the "
"host even if a port slipped into the spec by mistake."
msgstr ""
"对于永远不应发布到主机的服务（私有数据库、仅内部使用的 sidecar），只需**不列出任何端口**。与网络上的 `internal: true` "
"结合使用，即使规范中意外写入了端口，这些服务也无法从主机访问。"

#: src/container/networking.md:155
msgid "Single-network shorthand"
msgstr "单网络简写"

#: src/container/networking.md:157
msgid ""
"When every service joins the same network, you can put `networks: "
"['<name>']` on each service and `networks: { <name>: {...} }` once at the "
"root. The engine deduplicates network creation across services."
msgstr ""
"当所有服务加入同一网络时，可以在每个服务上写 `networks: ['<name>']`，并在根级写一次 `networks: { <name>: "
"{...} }`。引擎会对跨服务的网络创建进行去重。"

#: src/container/networking.md:161
msgid "Networks created in this session vs. external"
msgstr "本次会话创建的网络与外部网络"

#: src/container/networking.md:163
msgid ""
"Perry tracks **session networks** (created during this `up()` call) and "
"distinguishes them from `external: true` networks (assumed pre-existing and "
"shared across stacks). On `down()`, only session networks are torn down — "
"external networks are left alone, matching docker-compose semantics."
msgstr ""
"Perry 跟踪**会话网络**（在本次 `up()` 调用期间创建），并将其与 `external: true` 网络（假设已预先存在并跨 stack"
" 共享）区分开来。执行 `down()` 时，只有会话网络会被销毁——外部网络保持不变，与 docker-compose 的语义一致。"

#: src/container/networking.md:169
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"networks: {\n"
"  // Session: created if missing; removed on down()\n"
"  \"app-net\": { driver: \"bridge\" },\n"
"\n"
"  // External: must already exist; never touched on down()\n"
"  \"shared-public-net\": { external: true, name: \"external_pub_v1\" },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/networking.md:179
msgid "Network options for production"
msgstr "生产环境的网络选项"

#: src/container/networking.md:181
msgid "Common per-network knobs you'll want for production:"
msgstr "生产环境中常用的每个网络的配置项："

#: src/container/networking.md:183 src/i18n/interpolation.md:88
msgid "Pattern"
msgstr "模式"

#: src/container/networking.md:185
msgid "**Disable masquerade / NAT** (host-side)"
msgstr "**禁用 masquerade / NAT**（主机侧）"

#: src/container/networking.md:185
msgid ""
"`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.bridge.enable_ip_masquerade\": "
"\"false\" }`"
msgstr ""
"`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.bridge.enable_ip_masquerade\": "
"\"false\" }`"

#: src/container/networking.md:186
msgid "**Custom MTU** (matches host network)"
msgstr "**自定义 MTU**（与主机网络匹配）"

#: src/container/networking.md:186
msgid "`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.driver.mtu\": \"1450\" }`"
msgstr "`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.driver.mtu\": \"1450\" }`"

#: src/container/networking.md:187
msgid "**Stable bridge name** (for iptables rules)"
msgstr "**固定 bridge 名称**（用于 iptables 规则）"

#: src/container/networking.md:187
msgid "`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.bridge.name\": \"br-myapp\" }`"
msgstr "`driver_opts: { \"com.docker.network.bridge.name\": \"br-myapp\" }`"

#: src/container/networking.md:188
msgid "**Tag for monitoring**"
msgstr "**打标签以便监控**"

#: src/container/networking.md:188
msgid "`labels: { team: \"platform\", environment: \"prod\" }`"
msgstr "`labels: { team: \"platform\", environment: \"prod\" }`"

#: src/container/networking.md:192
msgid ""
"[Compose orchestration](./compose.md) — full `up()` / `down()` reference."
msgstr "[Compose 编排](./compose.md) — `up()` / `down()` 完整参考。"

#: src/container/networking.md:194
msgid ""
"[Production patterns](./production-patterns.md) — Forgejo example uses the "
"internal-db-net + public-web-net split."
msgstr ""
"[生产模式](./production-patterns.md) — Forgejo 示例使用了内部数据库网络 + 公共 Web 网络的分离方案。"

#: src/container/networking.md:196
msgid ""
"[Volumes](./volumes.md) — companion concept: networks without volumes is "
"rare in production stacks."
msgstr "[卷](./volumes.md) — 配套概念：生产 stack 中几乎不会只有网络而没有卷。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:3
msgid ""
"Container filesystems are ephemeral by default — once a container is "
"removed, anything written to its layers is gone. Production deployments need"
" volumes for the data that should survive container restarts + upgrades: "
"database storage, uploaded files, generated config, etc."
msgstr ""
"容器文件系统默认是临时的——一旦容器被删除，写入其层的所有内容都会消失。生产部署需要使用卷来存储应在容器重启和升级后保留的数据：数据库存储、上传的文件、生成的配置等。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:8
msgid "Perry supports the three Compose-spec volume modes:"
msgstr "Perry 支持 Compose 规范的三种卷模式："

#: src/container/volumes.md:10 src/cli/fast-math.md:9 src/cli/fast-math.md:129
msgid "Mode"
msgstr "模式"

#: src/container/volumes.md:10
msgid "Spec example"
msgstr "规范示例"

#: src/container/volumes.md:12
msgid "**Named volume**"
msgstr "**具名卷**"

#: src/container/volumes.md:12
msgid "`[\"app-pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\"]`"
msgstr "`[\"app-pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\"]`"

#: src/container/volumes.md:12
msgid "Database state, durable per-app data."
msgstr "数据库状态，按应用持久化的数据。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:13
msgid "**Bind mount**"
msgstr "**绑定挂载**"

#: src/container/volumes.md:13
msgid "`[\"./config:/app/config:ro\"]`"
msgstr "`[\"./config:/app/config:ro\"]`"

#: src/container/volumes.md:13
msgid "Host-supplied config or secrets."
msgstr "由主机提供的配置或密钥。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:14
msgid "**System pass-through**"
msgstr "**系统直通**"

#: src/container/volumes.md:14
msgid "`[\"/etc/timezone:/etc/timezone:ro\"]`"
msgstr "`[\"/etc/timezone:/etc/timezone:ro\"]`"

#: src/container/volumes.md:14
msgid "Read-only access to host system files."
msgstr "对主机系统文件的只读访问。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:16
msgid "Declaring named volumes"
msgstr "声明具名卷"

#: src/container/volumes.md:18
msgid ""
"Named volumes must be declared at the spec root and referenced by name in "
"each service's `volumes` array:"
msgstr "具名卷必须在规范根级声明，并在每个服务的 `volumes` 数组中按名称引用："

#: src/container/volumes.md:21
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const stack = await up({\n"
"  services: {\n"
"    db: {\n"
"      image: \"postgres:16-alpine\",\n"
"      volumes: [\"app-pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data\"],\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
"  volumes: {\n"
"    \"app-pgdata\": { driver: \"local\" },\n"
"  },\n"
"});\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/volumes.md:35
msgid "Recognised `ComposeVolume` fields:"
msgstr "支持的 `ComposeVolume` 字段："

#: src/container/volumes.md:39
msgid "Volume driver (`\"local\"` is the default)."
msgstr "卷驱动（默认为 `\"local\"`）。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:40
msgid "Don't create — assume the volume already exists."
msgstr "不创建——假设卷已存在。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:41
msgid "Override the volume's runtime name."
msgstr "覆盖卷的运行时名称。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:43
msgid "Bind mounts"
msgstr "绑定挂载"

#: src/container/volumes.md:45
msgid "For host-supplied data, use the `host:container[:options]` form:"
msgstr "对于由主机提供的数据，使用 `host:container[:options]` 格式："

#: src/container/volumes.md:47
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"volumes: [\n"
"  \"./config:/app/config:ro\",     // read-only config dir from host\n"
"  \"/var/log/myapp:/app/logs\",    // bidirectional logs\n"
"],\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/volumes.md:54
msgid ""
"Permissions are governed by the host filesystem and the container's running "
"UID. If the container runs as a non-root user (as it should — see "
"[Security](./security.md)), make sure the host directory is owned by a "
"matching UID, **or** explicitly set the container UID via `USER_UID` / "
"`USER_GID` env vars in the image (the Forgejo image does this)."
msgstr ""
"权限由主机文件系统和容器运行的 UID 决定。如果容器以非 root "
"用户运行（应当如此——参见[安全](./security.md)），请确保主机目录由匹配的 UID 拥有，**或者**通过镜像中的 `USER_UID`"
" / `USER_GID` 环境变量显式设置容器 UID（Forgejo 镜像即采用此方式）。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:61
msgid "System pass-throughs"
msgstr "系统直通"

#: src/container/volumes.md:63
msgid ""
"Read-only mounts of host system files are common for time / DNS / locale "
"alignment:"
msgstr "对主机系统文件的只读挂载常用于时区 / DNS / 本地化对齐："

#: src/container/volumes.md:66
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"volumes: [\n"
"  \"/etc/timezone:/etc/timezone:ro\",\n"
"  \"/etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro\",\n"
"],\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/volumes.md:73
msgid ""
"Best-effort: hosts where the source path doesn't exist (e.g. some minimal "
"Alpine VMs) just see a missing mount source — docker tolerates it; the "
"container falls back to UTC / system defaults."
msgstr ""
"尽力而为：在源路径不存在的主机上（例如某些精简版 Alpine 虚拟机），挂载源缺失——docker 会容忍此情况，容器回退使用 UTC / "
"系统默认值。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:77
msgid "Preservation on `down()`"
msgstr "`down()` 时的保留行为"

#: src/container/volumes.md:79
msgid "By default, **`down(handle)` preserves named volumes**:"
msgstr "默认情况下，**`down(handle)` 会保留具名卷**："

#: src/container/volumes.md:81
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"await down(stack);                       // containers + networks gone, volumes survive\n"
"await down(stack, { volumes: false });   // same — explicit preserve\n"
"await down(stack, { volumes: true });    // ⚠ volumes ALSO removed (DESTROYS DATA)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/volumes.md:87
msgid "This matches `docker compose down` semantics:"
msgstr "这与 `docker compose down` 的语义一致："

#: src/container/volumes.md:89
msgid "Command"
msgstr "命令"

#: src/container/volumes.md:89
msgid "Networks"
msgstr "网络"

#: src/container/volumes.md:91
msgid "`down(handle)`"
msgstr "`down(handle)`"

#: src/container/volumes.md:91 src/container/volumes.md:92
msgid "removed"
msgstr "已删除"

#: src/container/volumes.md:91
msgid "**kept**"
msgstr "**保留**"

#: src/container/volumes.md:92
msgid "`down(handle, { volumes: true })`"
msgstr "`down(handle, { volumes: true })`"

#: src/container/volumes.md:92
msgid "**removed**"
msgstr "**已删除**"

#: src/container/volumes.md:94
msgid ""
"After a `down(handle)`, you can `up(spec)` again with the same volume "
"declarations and the database / file state from before is still there. "
"That's how the [Forgejo example](./production-patterns.md) supports \"deploy"
" → tear-down → redeploy\" cycles without data loss."
msgstr ""
"执行 `down(handle)` 后，可以再次使用相同的卷声明执行 `up(spec)`，之前的数据库 / 文件状态仍然存在。这就是 [Forgejo"
" 示例](./production-patterns.md) 支持「部署 → 销毁 → 重新部署」循环而不丢失数据的原因。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:99
msgid ""
"⚠️ **Forgejo / Postgres redeploy gotcha:** if you used randomly generated "
"passwords or secret keys on the first deploy, **the next redeploy with new "
"random secrets will fail** because postgres authenticates against the old "
"password and Forgejo can't decrypt the existing config dir with a different "
"SECRET_KEY. For redeploys against the same volumes, set "
"`FORGEJO_DB_PASSWORD` / `FORGEJO_SECRET_KEY` / `FORGEJO_INTERNAL_TOKEN` to "
"**stable** values (e.g. via an `.env` file). The Forgejo example's doc-"
"comment has the canonical pattern."
msgstr ""
"⚠️ **Forgejo / Postgres 重新部署注意事项：** "
"如果您在首次部署时使用了随机生成的密码或密钥，**下次以新随机密钥重新部署将会失败**，因为 Postgres 会使用旧密码进行验证，而 Forgejo"
" 无法用不同的 `SECRET_KEY` 解密现有的配置目录。对于挂载相同卷的重新部署，请将 `FORGEJO_DB_PASSWORD` / "
"`FORGEJO_SECRET_KEY` / `FORGEJO_INTERNAL_TOKEN` 设置为**固定**值（例如通过 `.env` "
"文件）。Forgejo 示例的文档注释中有规范的写法。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:109
msgid "External volumes"
msgstr "外部卷"

#: src/container/volumes.md:111
msgid ""
"Mark a volume `external: true` to share it across stacks or to use a volume "
"created by a different process (e.g. `docker volume create team-shared-"
"cache` ahead of time):"
msgstr ""
"将卷标记为 `external: true`，可在多个 stack 之间共享，或使用由其他流程创建的卷（例如提前执行 `docker volume "
"create team-shared-cache`）："

#: src/container/volumes.md:115
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"volumes: {\n"
"  \"shared-cache\": { external: true, name: \"team-shared-cache\" },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/container/volumes.md:121
msgid ""
"External volumes are **never removed** by `down(handle, { volumes: true })` "
"— that flag only drops volumes the engine itself created. This matches "
"docker-compose semantics; if you want the external volume gone, remove it "
"explicitly with `docker volume rm team-shared-cache`."
msgstr ""
"外部卷**永远不会**被 `down(handle, { volumes: true })` 删除——该标志只会删除引擎自身创建的卷。这与 "
"docker-compose 语义一致；如需删除外部卷，请使用 `docker volume rm team-shared-cache` 显式移除。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:126
msgid "Volume naming and ownership"
msgstr "卷的命名与归属"

#: src/container/volumes.md:128
msgid ""
"Perry doesn't currently namespace volume names by project — the name you "
"write in the spec is the literal docker volume name. So `forgejo-pgdata` is "
"created as the docker volume `forgejo-pgdata`, and two stacks both declaring"
" `forgejo-pgdata` would share it."
msgstr ""
"Perry 目前不会按项目对卷名添加命名空间——您在 spec 中填写的名称就是实际的 docker 卷名称。因此 `forgejo-pgdata` "
"会被创建为 docker 卷 `forgejo-pgdata`，两个 stack 若都声明 `forgejo-pgdata` 则会共享同一个卷。"

#: src/container/volumes.md:133
msgid ""
"For multi-stack isolation, prefix the volume name with the project / stack "
"identifier:"
msgstr "如需多 stack 隔离，请在卷名中加上项目 / stack 标识符作为前缀："

#: src/container/volumes.md:136
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"volumes: {\n"
"  \"myapp-staging-pgdata\":   { driver: \"local\" },\n"
"  \"myapp-production-pgdata\": { driver: \"local\" },\n"
"},\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

