msgstr "11 ms"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:114
msgid ""
"Read these together: `--fast-math` produces a large speedup ONLY on loops "
"where the accumulator step is constant or trivially-redundant enough that "
"LLVM can split it into parallel partial sums. Real FP workloads rarely look "
"like `sum += 1` and so rarely benefit. The default mode beats Node on "
"`array_sum` and matches it on `dot_product` without giving up bit-exact "
"parity."
msgstr ""
"把这些数据放在一起看：`--fast-math` 仅在那些累加器步长是常量或微不足道地冗余、足以让 LLVM "
"将其拆分为并行部分和的循环上，才能产生大幅加速。真实的浮点工作负载很少看起来像 `sum += 1`，因此很少受益。默认模式在 `array_sum` "
"上击败 Node，并在 `dot_product` 上与之匹配，同时不放弃位级精确一致性。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:121
msgid "Correctness numbers"
msgstr "正确性数据"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:123
msgid ""
"`scripts/fp_fuzz.mjs` — randomly generates TS programs exercising the six "
"patterns most likely to trip per-instruction FMFs (left-fold, tree-fold, "
"right-fold reductions; FMA-shaped chains; algebraic identities like "
"`(a/b)*b`; cancellation predicates). Each program is compiled with both Node"
" and Perry, and stdout is diffed byte-for-byte."
msgstr ""
"`scripts/fp_fuzz.mjs` — 随机生成 TS 程序，使用最有可能触发按指令 FMF 的六种模式（左折叠、树折叠、右折叠归约；FMA "
"形状链；像 `(a/b)*b` 的代数恒等式；抵消谓词）。每个程序都用 Node 和 Perry 编译，并对 stdout 进行逐字节比对。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:129
msgid "Pass rate (100 random programs, seed=200)"
msgstr "通过率（100 个随机程序，seed=200）"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:131
msgid "94/100"
msgstr "94/100"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:132
msgid "~70/100"
msgstr "约 70/100"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:134
msgid ""
"The 6/100 default-mode failures are residual divergences from sources not "
"gated by per-instruction FMFs — most originate in the LLVM SLP vectorizer at"
" `-O3`, which can apply pairwise reduction even without the `reassoc` "
"permission. Tracked separately; out of scope for this flag."
msgstr ""
"默认模式 6/100 的失败是来自不受按指令 FMF 控制的源头的残余偏差——大多数源自 LLVM 在 `-O3` 下的 SLP 向量化器，即使没有 "
"`reassoc` 许可，它也可能应用成对归约。已单独跟踪；不在此标志的范围内。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:140
msgid "Object-cache interaction"
msgstr "对象缓存的交互"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:142
msgid ""
"Perry's per-module `.o` cache (in `.perry-cache/objects/`) keys on the "
"`fast_math` and `fp_contract` settings alongside source hash and other "
"compile options. Toggling either invalidates affected cache entries — `perry"
" --fast-math` or `perry --fp-contract=on` right after `perry` does a clean "
"recompile of every module that contains f64 arithmetic. No `--no-cache` "
"necessary."
msgstr ""
"Perry 的每模块 `.o` 缓存（位于 `.perry-cache/objects/`）以 `fast_math` 和 `fp_contract` "
"设置以及源码哈希和其他编译选项作为键。切换任意一项都会使受影响的缓存条目失效——在执行 `perry` 之后立即执行 `perry --fast-"
"math` 或 `perry --fp-contract=on`，会对所有包含 f64 运算的模块进行全量重新编译，无需使用 `--no-cache`。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:149
msgid ""
"(This is a deliberate fix. During the original investigation, an early "
"version of the flag forgot to enter the cache key, and the result was that "
"toggling the flag appeared to do nothing because all `.o` files came from "
"the cache. If you ever see fast-math defaults that _seem_ not to take "
"effect, suspect the cache key first.)"
msgstr ""
"（这是一个有意为之的修复。在最初的调查中，该标志的早期版本忘记将其纳入缓存键，结果是切换该标志看起来什么都没做，因为所有 `.o` "
"文件都来自缓存。如果你看到 fast-math 默认值_似乎_未生效，请首先怀疑缓存键。）"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:155
msgid "Migration notes"
msgstr "迁移说明"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:157
msgid ""
"**For library authors:** if your TS library publishes benchmark numbers, "
"document which mode you measured under. The 7× sum-loop case is the only "
"place the gap is large; if your benchmark doesn't look like that, the "
"numbers are mode-independent and you can publish one set."
msgstr ""
"**对于库作者：** 如果你的 TS 库发布了基准测试数据，请记录你测量时所处的模式。7 "
"倍的求和循环案例是差距大的唯一地方；如果你的基准测试不像那样，则数据与模式无关，你可以发布一组数据。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:162
msgid ""
"**For app authors:** there is no migration. Default behavior is the pre-flag"
" behavior with `--fast-math` removed; bit-exact results are _more_ "
"compatible with Node, not less."
msgstr ""
"**对于应用作者：** 无需迁移。默认行为是去除 `--fast-math` 之前的行为；位级精确结果与 Node _更_兼容，而非更不兼容。"

#: src/cli/fast-math.md:165
msgid ""
"**For determinism-critical code** (lockstep simulations, financial "
"reconciliation, hash function correctness): leave the default. Even with "
"`--fast-math` off there's a residual ~6% divergence rate on random FP code, "
"which is too high for true determinism work — but it's an order of magnitude"
" better than the ~30% with the flag on."
msgstr ""
"**对于确定性关键代码**（同步锁步仿真、金融对账、哈希函数正确性）：保持默认。即使关闭 `--fast-math`，在随机浮点代码上仍有约 6% "
"的残余偏差率，这对于真正的确定性工作来说太高了——但这比开启该标志时的约 30% 好一个数量级。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:1
msgid "Dynamic Stdlib Dispatch (`@perry-allow-dynamic`)"
msgstr "动态标准库分发（`@perry-allow-dynamic`）"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry refuses compile-time _dynamic dispatch_ on Node-core stdlib "
"namespaces. A call site like"
msgstr "Perry 拒绝在 Node 核心标准库命名空间上进行编译时 _动态分发_。类似以下的调用点"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:6
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const m = \"exit\";\n"
"(process as any)[m](0);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:11
msgid ""
"fails to compile. The check exists to catch the standard string-based "
"obfuscation pattern used by malicious npm packages: `process[\"bind\" + "
"\"ing\"](\"dns\")`, `globalThis[atob(\"ZXZhbA==\")]()`, `fs[methodName]()` "
"where `methodName` is computed at runtime."
msgstr ""
"将无法编译。此检查旨在捕获恶意 npm 包常用的字符串混淆模式：`process[\"bind\" + "
"\"ing\"](\"dns\")`、`globalThis[atob(\"ZXZhbA==\")]()`、`fs[methodName]()（其中 "
"`methodName` 在运行时计算）。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:16
msgid ""
"The pass is purely compile-time — **zero runtime cost** — and is on by "
"default. Issue [\\#503](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/503) tracks "
"the design."
msgstr ""
"该检查纯粹发生在编译时——**零运行时开销**——并默认启用。Issue "
"[\\#503](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/503) 跟踪该设计。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:20
msgid "What's checked"
msgstr "检查内容"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:22
msgid "Dynamic dispatch is refused when **all** of the following hold:"
msgstr "当以下**所有**条件成立时，动态分发将被拒绝："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:24
msgid ""
"The receiver resolves to a known Node-core stdlib namespace: `process`, "
"`fs`, `crypto`, `child_process`, `net`, `os`, `path`, `http`, `https`, "
"`http2`, `stream`, `url`, `util`, `events`, `dns`, `tls`, `querystring`, "
"`zlib`, `async_hooks`, `readline`, `string_decoder`, `tty`, "
"`worker_threads`."
msgstr ""
"接收者解析为已知的 Node "
"核心标准库命名空间：`process`、`fs`、`crypto`、`child_process`、`net`、`os`、`path`、`http`、`https`、`http2`、`stream`、`url`、`util`、`events`、`dns`、`tls`、`querystring`、`zlib`、`async_hooks`、`readline`、`string_decoder`、`tty`、`worker_threads`。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:29
msgid ""
"The index expression is _not_ a string literal — `fs[\"readFileSync\"]` is "
"treated identically to `fs.readFileSync` and always passes."
msgstr ""
"索引表达式_不是_字符串字面量——`fs[\"readFileSync\"]` 与 `fs.readFileSync` 处理方式完全相同，始终通过检查。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:31
msgid "The user has not opted out (see below)."
msgstr "用户未选择退出（见下文）。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:33
msgid "User-code reflection on user-defined objects is unaffected:"
msgstr "用户代码对用户自定义对象的反射操作不受影响："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:35
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const me = { greet: (n: string) => \"hi \" + n };\n"
"const k = \"greet\";\n"
"me[k](\"world\"); // ✓ user object, not a stdlib namespace\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:41
msgid "Opt-outs"
msgstr "退出选项"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:43
msgid "The error message lists the available opt-outs in priority order:"
msgstr "错误信息按优先级列出可用的退出选项："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:45
msgid "1. Replace with a static call"
msgstr "1. 替换为静态调用"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:47
msgid ""
"The preferred fix. The check exists precisely because static calls are "
"auditable."
msgstr "首选修复方式。该检查的存在正是因为静态调用是可审计的。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:50
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"process.exit(0);                // ✓\n"
"fs.readFileSync(\"/tmp/x\");       // ✓\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:55
msgid "2. `// @perry-allow-dynamic` annotation (host code only)"
msgstr "2. `// @perry-allow-dynamic` 注释（仅限宿主代码）"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:57
msgid ""
"For legitimate one-off dispatch in your own code, drop a line comment on or "
"immediately above the offending site:"
msgstr "对于你自己代码中合理的一次性分发需求，可在违规调用点上方或同一行添加行注释："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:60
msgid ""
"```typescript,no-test\n"
"const k = pickHandler();\n"
"// @perry-allow-dynamic\n"
"(process as any)[k](0);\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:66
msgid ""
"Contiguous comment lines above the call also count, so the annotation can "
"sit alongside an `// @ts-ignore` or similar."
msgstr "调用上方连续的注释行也计入在内，因此该注释可与 `// @ts-ignore` 或类似注释并列使用。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:69
msgid ""
"The annotation is honored **only in host source files** (anything not under "
"`node_modules/`). A dependency cannot grant itself the opt-out by writing "
"`// @perry-allow-dynamic` next to its own call — that would defeat the "
"supply-chain defense the check exists for. Dependencies opt in via the "
"host's per-package allow list (below) or the global flag. Tracked in "
"[\\#996](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/996)."
msgstr ""
"该注释**仅在宿主源文件中生效**（即不在 `node_modules/` 下的任何文件）。依赖项不能通过在自身调用旁写 `// @perry-"
"allow-dynamic` "
"来自行授予退出权限——这会破坏该检查所保护的供应链防御机制。依赖项需通过宿主的按包允许列表（见下文）或全局标志来选择退出。相关跟踪见 "
"[\\#996](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/996)。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:76
msgid "3. Per-package allow list in `package.json`"
msgstr "3. 在 `package.json` 中配置按包允许列表"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:78
msgid ""
"To opt one or more npm dependencies out, list them under "
"`perry.allowDynamicStdlibDispatch` in the **host** application's "
"`package.json`:"
msgstr ""
"若要让一个或多个 npm 依赖退出检查，请在**宿主**应用的 `package.json` 中，将其列在 "
"`perry.allowDynamicStdlibDispatch` 下："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:85 src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:100
msgid "\"allowDynamicStdlibDispatch\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:85
msgid "\"legacy-dep\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:85
msgid "\"@scope/other-dep\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:90
msgid ""
"Modules whose source path lives under `node_modules/<pkg>/…` are matched "
"against this list. Host code is _not_ covered — opting host code out "
"requires the global flag below or the site annotation."
msgstr ""
"源路径位于 `node_modules/<pkg>/…` "
"下的模块将与此列表进行匹配。宿主代码_不在_覆盖范围内——要让宿主代码退出，需使用下方的全局标志或站点注释。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:95
msgid "4. Global opt-out"
msgstr "4. 全局退出"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:97
msgid "To disable the check across the entire build, set the boolean form:"
msgstr "若要在整个构建中禁用该检查，请设置布尔形式："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:103
msgid "…or set the env var for a one-off build:"
msgstr "……或者为单次构建设置环境变量："

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:109
msgid ""
"CI can enforce the check by setting `PERRY_ALLOW_DYNAMIC_STDLIB=0`, which "
"beats any package.json opt-out."
msgstr ""
"CI 可通过设置 `PERRY_ALLOW_DYNAMIC_STDLIB=0` 来强制启用该检查，此设置优先于任何 package.json "
"中的退出配置。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:112
msgid "Why on by default"
msgstr "默认启用的原因"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:114
msgid ""
"The check is the cheapest possible defense against the dispatch-by-string "
"class of supply-chain evasion. The cost to legitimate code is essentially "
"zero — static calls and literal-keyed access compile unchanged. Code that "
"genuinely needs the indirection has four ways to say so explicitly, and the "
"failure mode is a build error rather than a silent miss in detection."
msgstr ""
"该检查是对抗字符串分发类供应链逃逸的最低成本防御手段。对合法代码的代价几乎为零——静态调用和字面量键访问编译行为不变。真正需要间接调用的代码有四种方式可以明确声明，而失败模式是构建错误，而非检测中的静默遗漏。"

#: src/cli/dynamic-dispatch.md:121
msgid ""
"See [`#503`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/503) for design "
"discussion and the broader supply-chain hardening series "
"(\\[`#495`–`#506`\\] "
"(https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3Aenhancement+security))."
msgstr ""
"参见 [`#503`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/503) "
"了解设计讨论以及更广泛的供应链加固系列（\\[`#495`–`#506`\\] "
"(https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3Aenhancement+security)）。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:1
msgid "JS Runtime Opt-In (`perry.allowJsRuntime`)"
msgstr "JS 运行时选择性启用（`perry.allowJsRuntime`）"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry refuses to link `perry-jsruntime` — the QuickJS-based runtime that "
"executes interpreted `.js` files from `node_modules/` — unless the host "
"application has explicitly opted in. This protects Perry's primary "
"structural advantage over Node: a Perry binary normally contains _no_ JS "
"evaluator at all."
msgstr ""
"Perry 拒绝链接 `perry-jsruntime`——这是基于 QuickJS 的运行时，用于执行来自 `node_modules/` 的解释型 "
"`.js` 文件——除非宿主应用已明确选择启用。这保护了 Perry 相对于 Node 的核心结构优势：Perry 二进制文件通常_完全不包含_ JS "
"解释器。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:9
msgid "The check fires at compile time. **Zero runtime cost.**"
msgstr "该检查在编译时触发。**零运行时开销。**"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:11 src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:14
msgid "How a build hits this"
msgstr "构建如何触发此问题"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:13
msgid ""
"The Perry compiler routes any `.js`/`.cjs`/`.mjs` file from `node_modules/` "
"through `perry-jsruntime`'s QuickJS sandbox instead of the native LLVM "
"backend. Most npm packages are pure-JS, so transitive deps can pull the "
"runtime in without the host author noticing — a silent regression of Perry's"
" main hardening pitch."
msgstr ""
"Perry 编译器将来自 `node_modules/` 的任何 `.js`/`.cjs`/`.mjs` 文件通过 `perry-jsruntime` "
"的 QuickJS 沙箱路由，而非原生 LLVM 后端。大多数 npm 包是纯 "
"JS，因此传递依赖可能在宿主作者未察觉的情况下引入运行时——这悄无声息地回退了 Perry 的主要安全加固特性。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:19
msgid "When that happens without an opt-in, the build fails with:"
msgstr "当在未选择启用的情况下发生这种情况时，构建将失败并报错："

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:32
msgid ""
"The diagnostic lists every file that triggered the pull-in, capped at the "
"first eight, with the owning npm package (when the path resolves through "
"`node_modules/<pkg>/`)."
msgstr ""
"诊断信息列出了每个触发引入的文件，最多显示前八个，并附有所属 npm 包名（当路径通过 `node_modules/<pkg>/` 解析时）。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:36 src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:46
msgid "Opt-in mechanisms"
msgstr "启用机制"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:38
msgid "Three equivalent ways, listed in priority order:"
msgstr "三种等效方式，按优先级排列："

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:40
msgid "1. `perry.allowJsRuntime` in `package.json` (persistent)"
msgstr "1. `package.json` 中的 `perry.allowJsRuntime`（持久化）"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:45
msgid "\"allowJsRuntime\""
msgstr ""

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:50
msgid ""
"Recommended for production builds where you've reviewed the JS deps and "
"decided to ship them. The setting lives in source control next to the "
"dependency list it affects."
msgstr "推荐用于生产构建，适用于已审查 JS 依赖并决定将其一并发布的场景。该设置与其影响的依赖列表一起保存在版本控制中。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:54
msgid "2. `--enable-js-runtime` CLI flag (per-invocation)"
msgstr "2. `--enable-js-runtime` CLI 标志（单次调用）"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:60
msgid ""
"Treated as an explicit per-build opt-in. Useful for local development or "
"one-off builds against a host that intentionally doesn't set "
"`allowJsRuntime: true`."
msgstr "视为单次构建的明确选择启用。适用于本地开发或针对有意未设置 `allowJsRuntime: true` 的宿主进行的一次性构建。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:64
msgid "3. `PERRY_ALLOW_JS_RUNTIME=1` env var (CI-friendly)"
msgstr "3. `PERRY_ALLOW_JS_RUNTIME=1` 环境变量（CI 友好）"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:70
msgid ""
"`=1`/`true` opts in; `=0`/`false` keeps the refusal on even if "
"`package.json` opted in — useful as a CI gate that fails closed when someone"
" tries to merge an opt-in by accident."
msgstr ""
"`=1`/`true` 表示选择启用；`=0`/`false` 即使 `package.json` 中已选择启用也保持拒绝——适合用作 CI "
"门控，在有人误将选择启用合入时使构建失败关闭。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:74
msgid "Lockdown mode"
msgstr "锁定模式"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:76
msgid ""
"This refusal will be part of the deny-set for the upcoming `--lockdown` "
"compile flag (issue [`#496`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/496)). "
"In lockdown mode, no opt-in is honored — the build always refuses `perry-"
"jsruntime` linkage."
msgstr ""
"此拒绝行为将纳入即将推出的 `--lockdown` 编译标志的拒绝集（issue "
"[`#496`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/496)）。在锁定模式下，任何选择启用均不被接受——构建始终拒绝链接"
" `perry-jsruntime`。"

#: src/cli/allow-js-runtime.md:84
msgid ""
"[`#499`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/499) — design discussion."
msgstr "[`#499`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/499) — 设计讨论。"

