#: src/cli/capabilities.md:61
msgid "Diagnostic"
msgstr "诊断信息"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:63
msgid ""
"A failing build prints a combined diagnostic across every refused call site "
"(capped at the first 12 entries to keep output reasonable):"
msgstr "构建失败时会打印覆盖所有被拒绝调用点的综合诊断信息（最多显示前 12 条以保持输出合理）："

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:77
msgid ""
"The output names the owning package, the call kind, the source span, and the"
" missing token — enough to either (a) extend the allow-list, (b) set `\"*\":"
" [\"<token>\"]` for a wider default, or (c) replace the dep with one that "
"doesn't need the capability."
msgstr ""
"输出会注明所属包、调用类型、源码位置以及缺失的令牌——足以让你（a）扩展允许列表，（b）设置 `\"*\": [\"<token>\"]` "
"作为更宽泛的默认值，或（c）用不需要该能力的依赖替换现有依赖。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:82
msgid "Recommended workflow"
msgstr "推荐工作流"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:84
msgid ""
"**Start empty.** Set `\"permissions\": {}` to confirm your build is "
"currently passing without the pass active."
msgstr "**从空配置开始。** 设置 `\"permissions\": {}` 以确认当前构建在该遍历未激活时可以通过。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:86
msgid ""
"**Flip the default to deny.** Add `\"*\": []` and rebuild. The diagnostic "
"enumerates every capability your dep tree currently reaches."
msgstr "**将默认值切换为拒绝。** 添加 `\"*\": []` 并重新构建。诊断信息会枚举你的依赖树当前涉及的所有能力。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:89
msgid ""
"**Grant minimum tokens per dep.** Use the diagnostic to populate "
"`permissions` with the smallest token set each package needs."
msgstr "**按依赖授予最少令牌。** 使用诊断信息，为每个包填充所需的最小令牌集到 `permissions`。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:91
msgid ""
"**Lock in CI.** Once the build is green with the explicit permissions, leave"
" it that way — new deps that want new tokens show up as build failures, "
"surfacing in the PR review."
msgstr ""
"**在 CI 中固定配置。** 一旦构建在显式权限下通过，保持此状态不变——需要新令牌的新依赖会以构建失败的形式出现，在 PR 审查中浮现。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:95
msgid "Relationship to other security flags"
msgstr "与其他安全标志的关系"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:97
msgid ""
"**`--lockdown` (#496)** — gates host code itself against the arbitrary-code-"
"execution surfaces (perry-jsruntime, `perry.nativeLibrary` archives, "
"`child_process.*`). Orthogonal: `perry.permissions` is per-dep, `--lockdown`"
" is whole-binary."
msgstr ""
"**`--lockdown`（#496）** —— 对宿主代码本身针对任意代码执行接口（perry-"
"jsruntime、`perry.nativeLibrary` "
"归档文件、`child_process.*`）进行限制。两者正交：`perry.permissions` 是按依赖的，`--lockdown` "
"是针对整个二进制的。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:101
msgid ""
"**`allowedHosts` (#502)** — narrows `net:fetch` from \"any URL\" to \"URLs "
"matching this allow-list.\" A dep with `net:fetch` permission still has to "
"clear the egress allow-list at every call site."
msgstr ""
"**`allowedHosts`（#502）** —— 将 `net:fetch` 从\"任意 URL\"收窄为\"匹配此允许列表的 URL\"。拥有 "
"`net:fetch` 权限的依赖在每个调用点仍需通过出口允许列表的检查。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:104
msgid ""
"**`PERRY_SANDBOX_BUILDRS` (#505)** — sandboxes the _build-time_ `build.rs` "
"scripts. `perry.permissions` controls what the _runtime_ binary can do."
msgstr ""
"**`PERRY_SANDBOX_BUILDRS`（#505）** —— 对_构建时_的 `build.rs` "
"脚本进行沙箱处理。`perry.permissions` 控制的是_运行时_二进制文件的能力。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:110
msgid ""
"[`#501`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/501) — design discussion."
msgstr "[`#501`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/501) —— 设计讨论。"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:111
msgid "[`--lockdown`](./lockdown.md)"
msgstr "[`--lockdown`](./lockdown.md)"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:112
msgid "[Egress Allowlist (`allowedHosts`)](./allowed-hosts.md)"
msgstr "[出口允许列表（`allowedHosts`）](./allowed-hosts.md)"

#: src/cli/capabilities.md:113
